8 An Act relating to schools; defining terms; requiring
boards of education to request a national criminal
9 history record check for volunteers beginning in
certain school year; directing the Oklahoma State
10 Bureau of Investigation to obtain fingerprints and
require payment of certain fee; providing for deposit
11 of fee into certain fund; allowing reimbursement of
certain search cost; requiring boards of education to
12 publish certain notice on certain website; providing
certain exceptions; providing for codification;
13 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-142.2 of Title 70, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. For the purposes of this section, “board of education”
21 includes a school district board of education, a private school
22 board of education, and the governing body of a charter school.
23 B. Except as otherwise provided in subsection E of this
24 section, beginning with the 2025-2026 school year, a board of
Req. No. 1787 Page 1

1 educ ation shall request that the Oklahoma State Bureau of
2 Investigation (OSBI) provide a national criminal history record
3 check for a volunteer prior to the individual volunteering at the
4 school district, charter school, or private school site that the
5 board of education oversees. For the purposes of this section,
6 “national criminal history record check” shall have the same meaning
7 as provided for in Section 150.9 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma
8 Statutes. OSBI shall obtain fingerprints of the volunteer and
9 require that the person pay a search fee not to exceed Fifty Dollars
10 ($50.00) or the cost of the search, whichever is the lesser amount.
11 The fee shall be deposited into the OSBI Revolving Fund created
12 pursuant to Section 150.19a of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
13 C. A board of education may reimburse a volunteer for the cost
14 of the search required by subsection B of this section.
15 D. Each board of education shall publish on its website notice
16 of the national criminal history record check required by subsection
17 B of this section and whether the board of education provides
18 reimbursement for the cost of the search, as allowed by subsection C
19 of this section.
20 E. Volunteers who meet the criteria provided for in subsection
21 F of Section 5-142 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes may not be
22 required to have a national criminal history record check.
23 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
